    <h3>Our Mission</h3>
    <p>Graffiti Ministries is a faith-based, community focused organization serving the Coney Island community located in Brooklyn, New York City. Our calling is to serve our community in tangible ways, with a desire to play a role in helping our neighbors accomplish their goals and achieve their full potential.</p>

    <h3>Our History</h3>
    <p>Graffiti Coney Island is one of seven independent, affiliated Graffiti ministry sites and churches in a network serving communities of need across New York City and elsewhere. Graffiti began its work in 1975 by serving children in the drug-controlled culture of Manhattan's Lower East Side, and since then Graffiti's mission has been to bring people into fellowship with Christ and equip them in clear thinking, fair living, and true devotion. With a heart to see God's kingdom expand, Graffiti has assisted in some way in the starting of 60 new churches and ministry centers.</p>

    <h3>Our Beliefs</h3>
    <p>Graffiti Ministries is a Christian, bible-based organization. We believe that God has created the world around us and loves dearly each and every person who calls it home. We believe God displayed this love to mankind through the redemptive work of Jesus upon the cross, and this same redemption is available to all would accept it.</p>

